Classes.Summary:
GNInbound - Handles inbound file processing for Loads and Bales tables.
    
     Using Inbound.AlsoTable() to include additional row data from other tables:
     To reduce database queries during batch record checks, use the simplified Inbound.AlsoTable() API
     to fetch related tables via SQL JOINs.
    
     Example implementation in GinPreRead() (see line 274):
       Inbound.AlsoTable(AppChildTypes.BalesTable, AppChildTypes.LoadsTable, "Loads.LoadNumber = Bales.LoadNumber", "TotalBales");
    
     Parameters: (mainTableTypeID, relatedTableTypeID, joinCondition, columnsToSelect)
     The mainTable name is automatically replaced with "main" in the join condition.
     Use "*" for columnsToSelect to fetch all columns from the related table.
    
     Related data is accessible in BeforeBalesInbound/AfterBalesInbound via ExistingRecordRow columns
     with prefixes using the table name (e.g. "Loads_TotalBales", "Recaps_InvoiceNumber").
